folder: Bushwick Avenue & Himrod Street, Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1)
Bushwick Ave., at the N.E corner of Himrod Street. A view of the So. Bushwick Reformed Church. In the extreme foreground, is the head of Kossuth Place.

March 29, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, from another angle.

March 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3)
The same, seen from across Himrod Street. This edifice known as the "White Church" was organized November 6, 1851 and the building erected in February 1853 upon land donated by Andrew and Abram Stockholm in a community then known at Bowronville. The Sunday school was added to this church in 1881.

March 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Colleciton.
